# pyenv
#   For a library or package, you might want to ignore these files since the user is
#   responsible for setting up their own environment. For a binary, it's common to
#   include them.
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if delegates have different platforms, you may let Pipfile.lock ignored.
#   Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, poetry.lock can be either shared or ignored.
#   poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, pdm.lock can be either shared or ignored.
#   pdm.lock

